      <h1>Obesity Epidemic in Taiwan</h1>
      <p>
        Taiwan has seen a significant rise in obesity rates in recent years.
        According to the Taiwan Ministry of Health and Welfare, the obesity rate
        among adults increased from 28.7% in 2017 to 31.8% in 2021. A major
        factor contributing to this rise is the increased consumption of
        high-calorie, sugar-laden beverages like bubble tea. Obesity is a major
        risk factor for developing type 2 diabetes, and with more people turning
        to sugary drinks like bubble tea daily, the trend is becoming
        concerning.
      </p>
