      <h1>Diabetes Prevalence in Taiwan</h1>
      <p>
        Type 2 diabetes is also on the rise in Taiwan. In 2020, the Taiwan
        Diabetes Association reported that 11% of the population over the age of
        18 had diabetes, with an additional 20% being pre-diabetic. This is
        higher than the global average, and excessive sugar consumption, along
        with a lack of physical activity, plays a major role. Bubble tea’s high
        sugar content contributes to insulin resistance, a precursor to
        diabetes, with nearly 2 million people in Taiwan currently living with
        the condition.
      </p>
